        best_for: ['Agile Growth Marketers executing massive data-scraping and lead-enrichment operations', 'Non-Technical Founders attempting to build live, API-connected applications and dashboards', 'Operations Analysts terrified by the massive complexity of legacy Excel Macros and VBA', 'Teams wanting to publicly share highly beautiful, interactive data sets without looking like a boring 1990s accounting firm'],
        pros: ['The absolute, staggering architectural victory of "Native Integrations"; completely eradicating the requirement for third-party middleware (like Zapier) to pull Stripe or Salesforce data into a grid is a monumental time-saver', 'The visually stunning aesthetic architecture; publishing a Rows document creates a massive, modern, clean web experience that completely avoids the depressing, utilitarian UI of a massive Excel file', 'The "AI Analyst" fundamentally democratizes massive data science; forcing an AI to do the terrifying mathematical heavy lifting of generating a complex Pivot Table saves hours of absolute frustration for standard users'],
